						               													<description>Takeda Kawankajima 1553-1564 is part of the Age Of Battles table-top miniatures gaming system using 1/72 scale miniatures and the Shogun rule set. Takeda Kawankajima 1553-1564 allows you to play the five battles that took place on the plain of Kawanakajima.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The boxed game set includes everything needed to play out the five battles as a campaign:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Two complete armies in tan &amp;amp; grey&amp;#10;- 88 Samurai Infantry - tan/grey (8017)&amp;#10;- 34 Samurai Cavalry - tan/grey  (8025)&amp;#10;- 56 Samurai Army Headquarters figures &amp;amp; two honjins w/accessories - tan/grey (8029)&amp;#10;- 1 exclusive General Uesugi Kenshin mounted figure - tan&amp;#10;16 Regiment Cards&amp;#10;16 Regiment Stands w/flags&amp;#10;2 D20 dice&amp;#10;2 Rulers&amp;#10;1 Pen&amp;#10;1 Angle Pattern&amp;#10;1 Shogun Rule Book&amp;#10;1 Campaign/Historical Background Booklet&amp;#10;&amp;#10;From the back of the box:&amp;#10;This game allows playing the episodes of the battles having become the plot base of many films and books about the medieval Japan. In the second half of the 16th century on the Kawanakajima plain two armies under the leadership of two famous Japanese commanders. Takeda Shingen and Uesugi Kenshin, each strived for the supreme power, went into bloody battle.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Zvezda 8239&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
